title: Two dead, child critical after Vic crash
text:
Two people are dead and a boy is fighting for life after a multi-car smash in regional Victoria.

Up to three cars collided on the Bacchus Marsh-Geelong Road in Balliang on Sunday about 1pm, before a man and a woman, from different vehicles, died at the scene, police say.

A child has been taken to the Royal Children's Hospital in a critical condition, suffering a head injury, while a man, aged in his 40s, has been taken to a Geelong hospital in a serious but stable condition, Ambulance Victoria says.
